<div class="post-date">Oct 21</div>
<h2><a https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/1166.html" title="New kitchen, still no kitchen"> New kitchen, still no kitchen</a></h2>

<div class="entry">


     

  	<p>Our friends, who have three kids and a mother moving in, just bought a bigger house (no surprise there). They are now trying to get the place ready to move in which is taking quite a bit of work.</p>

	<p>One of the things they are doing is totally redoing the kitchen, tearing everything out and starting over from scratch. Hearing this we said &#8220;hmmm&#8230;.&#8221;</p>

	<p>As a result, we bought all their old cabinets, their refrigerator, sink, dishwasher and double oven. It wasn&#8217;t a bad deal.</p>

	<p>Last night and today we yanked them all out, dragged them over to our place, hauled them up to the third floor where they will sit until sometime next year when we have the ability to abandon our kitchen for the two weeks it&#8217;ll take to redo our kitchen.</p>

	<p>At least we get to use our &#8220;new&#8221; refrigerator until then. It&#8217;s the first refrigerator we&#8217;ve ever &#8220;owned.&#8221; We&#8217;ve been borrowing an extra from a friend and before that everywhere we lived came with a frige. </p>

	<p>Is there some phrase to the effect.. &#8220;you know you&#8217;re married when&#8230;&#8221; ? It took us 15 years, but hey.</p>


 
<div class="line"></div>

